29.11.2017

Data of gas generation by different microbial consortia in 4 biodegradation experiments

Aims

  • To visualise and evaluate data with different models,
  • to estimate the speed, maximum rate and the lag phase of methanogenesis.

Import data

Katse <- "28.02.2016_katse_metaanitekke_andmed.csv"
Tabel <- read.delim(Katse, sep = ";", dec = ",")
head(Tabel)
##   Aeg.p Katse.26 Katse.28 Katse.29 Katse.30
## 1  0.00 0.00e+00 0.00e+00 0.00e+00 0.00e+00
## 2  0.04 4.35e-06 2.97e-06 2.85e-06 2.46e-06
## 3  0.08 5.32e-06 4.77e-06 4.63e-06 4.00e-06
## 4  0.12 6.45e-06 6.36e-06 6.52e-06 4.62e-06
## 5  0.16 6.61e-06 8.48e-06 7.47e-06 4.62e-06
## 6  0.19 4.19e-06 9.32e-06 8.30e-06 4.93e-06

Methanogenesis in experiment 26

library(ggplot2)
Gr_katse26 <- ggplot(data = Tabel, aes(x = Aeg.p, y = Katse.26, group = 1)) +
  geom_line() +
  labs(x = "Aeg, päeva", y = "Metaani ml/g", title = "Katse 26")
Gr_katse26

We fit the data of experiment 26 with linear function

x1 <- Tabel[, 1]  
y1 <- Tabel[, 2]  
lineaarne_mudel <- nls(y1 ~ b*x1 + d)  
summary(lineaarne_mudel)  
## 
## Formula: y1 ~ b * x1 + d
## 
## Parameters:
##   Estimate Std. Error t value Pr(>|t|)    
## b 0.275042   0.003083  89.213   <2e-16 ***
## d 0.197021   0.117013   1.684   0.0924 .  
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
## 
## Residual standard error: 2.415 on 1623 degrees of freedom
## 
## Number of iterations to convergence: 1 
## Achieved convergence tolerance: 1.434e-07

Let us plot the fitted experimental data

b <- 0.1771  
d <- 0.4629  
x <-  0:70   
y <- b * x + d  
plot(y ~ x, type="l", xlab = "Time, days", ylab = "Methan, mL/g", 
    ylim = c(-5, 15))

Fitted the data of experiment 26 with linear function

knitr::include_graphics("Katse26_lineaarne.png")

We fit the data of experiment 26 with square function

x1 <- Tabel[, 1]  
y1 <- Tabel[, 2]  
ruut_mudel <- nls(y1 ~ a*x1*x1 + b*x1 + d)  
summary(ruut_mudel)  
## 
## Formula: y1 ~ a * x1 * x1 + b * x1 + d
## 
## Parameters:
##    Estimate Std. Error t value Pr(>|t|)    
## a 1.559e-03  3.699e-05   42.14   <2e-16 ***
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
## 
## Residual standard error: 2.934 on 1624 degrees of freedom
## 
## Number of iterations to convergence: 1 
## Achieved convergence tolerance: 3.663e-07

Let us plot the fitted experimental data

a <- -0.4909  
b <- 3.1927  
d <- -3.0436  
x <-  0:70  
y <-  a * x * x + b * x + d  
plot(y ~ x, type = "l",xlab = "Time, days", ylab = "Methan mL/g",ylim = c(-2500, 5))
